commit.message:
Remove the redundant configure check for cpuid.h

cpuid2cpuflags requires cpuid.h on x86 unconditionally, and the only
result of configure not finding it is a different error message,
so just remove the check and let the compiler fail the usual way.

Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>

commit.message:
Add FreeBSD/arm{,64} support

- Replace getauxval(3), a non-standard glibc extension, with
  FreeBSD's native elf_aux_info(3)
- Return features supported by the specific machine processor
  architecture (uname -p) rather than the hardware platform
  (uname -m), because the latter is too vague on FreeBSD and
  does not include specific version (generation)

Closes: https://github.com/mgorny/cpuid2cpuflags/pull/20
Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>
